Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["ii. Generic quantum state tools", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.974664564037022*^9, {3.9746646043779297`*^9, 3.974664609640778*^9}, {
   3.974664960965138*^9, 
   3.974664961506047*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"46d98bd7-3bd8-4697-955d-\
ca28d9c6b9ed"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Description", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0c5e9405-ffc8-425f-8a61-6cd9e625e1dd"],

Cell["\<\
This section defines generic functions for manipulating quantum states, i.e., \
kets in a Hilbert space of arbitrary dimensionality. The functions are \
intended to mimic the way calculations would be done by hand. In general, it \
is assumed that the quantum numbers enumerate a LINEARLY INDEPENDENT basis.

Thus, a \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]State,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] which is a \
linear combination of basis states and amplitudes, is represented as a list \
of \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Terms.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] Any given Term is \
composed of two parts:
i) A set of quantum numbers in the underlying linearly independent basis, and
ii) a c-number amplitude.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.974665329070407*^9, 3.974665375069374*^9}, 
   3.974665824107503*^9, {3.9747868713761168`*^9, 
   3.974786882942052*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e9944019-f63b-42e2-b1aa-\
b2fe48aea089"],

Cell["\<\
Example: For the simple harmonic oscillator, consider the unnormalized state \
|0> + i |1> - |2>. In the occupation number basis we identify three \
constituent Terms: {{0}, 1} and {{1},i} and {{2},-1}. The State would then be \
expressed as {{{0}, 1},{{1},i},{{2},-1}}.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.974665386997302*^9, 3.974665395224169*^9}, 
   3.974665427131302*^9},ExpressionUUID->"86463422-ccdd-4592-82c1-\
ab3d54e92c5a"],

Cell["\<\
Note: The script has been written for use with amplitudes that are complex \
NUMBERS. Some functions may not behave as expected when amplitudes contain \
unassigned VARIABLES.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.974665493141072*^9, 
  3.97466551535793*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ab3a8a66-997a-4b23-8217-\
6b9ea4afd600"],

Cell["\<\
Functions that are provided are intended to be applied to either a Term or a \
State(s), and the functions are named as Term[...] or State[...] to indicate \
this.
- Example: TermFlip takes a Term and returns a Term whose amplitude has a \
relative minus sign.
- Example: StateFlip takes a State and returns a State with all constituent \
Terms having a relative minus sign in their amplitudes.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.974665631996243*^9, 
  3.974665635263303*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8bd1b1ff-8262-4d48-9aa5-\
b5957ce82bc1"],

Cell["\<\
IMPORTANT: The result of a generic Term(...) function may be another Term OR \
a State OR something else, but the output of a generic State(...) function \
will almost NEVER be a Term. Usually, the output of a State(...) function is \
a State. Many bugs that arose when developing this script could be traced to \
assuming the wrong output type (Term or State) from some function. When in \
doubt, read the comments or function definitions to determine the form of the \
output.
- Example: TermQuery takes a Term and returns a boolean value.
- Example: TermScale takes a Term and returns a Term.
- Example: StateAdd takes two States and returns a State.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.974665730767177*^9, 3.9746657389322987`*^9}, {
  3.974787014185436*^9, 
  3.974787015085232*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d7c3c159-31b7-4dca-89d2-\
a15ac315362e"],

Cell["\<\
OFTEN, it is Term(...) functions where the real coding and logic takes place. \
State(...) functions are often just a mapping of the hand-written Term(...) \
function over all Terms in a given State, or they are directly composed from \
other State(...) functions. Sometimes, a function only makes sense for \
States, so only a State(...) version is available.
- Example: StateConsolidateTerms looks through a list of Terms for Terms that \
have identical quantum numbers, and consolidates like terms into single terms \
with all the amplitudes summed up.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9747870158522673`*^9, 
  3.974787032319346*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"031da3f8-b3dc-4771-aff8-\
4fc42df9e9db"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Generic quantum-state tool definitions", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9746658869178257`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"ad6f2e95-aa14-4551-ac17-\
e3dc81f5f0e5"],

Cell["\<\
Note: In the Mathematica implementation...
- A \"Term\" is a List with two elements
- Element [[1]] of the Term is a List containing the quantum numbers
- Element [[2]] of the Term is an amplitude
- A \"State\" is a List of Terms. An empty List is equivalent to the null \
state.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7a908422-8d70-4af1-88c4-1eeef3dd0c70"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"TermConjugate", "[", "term_", "]"}], ":=", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"term", "[", 
      RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"Conjugate", "[", 
      RowBox[{"term", "[", 
       RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StateConjugate", "[", "state_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
     RowBox[{"TermConjugate", ",", "state"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], 
  "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"TermScale", "[", 
    RowBox[{"const_", ",", "term_"}], "]"}], ":=", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
    "scale", " ", "the", " ", "amplitude", " ", "of", " ", "a", " ", "term", 
     " ", "by", " ", "some", " ", "constant"}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"term", "[", 
      RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"const", "*", 
      RowBox[{"term", "[", 
       RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}]}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"TermScale", "[", "const_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"TermScale", "[", 
      RowBox[{"const", ",", "#"}], "]"}], "&"}]}], ";"}], "\n"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"StateScale", "[", 
    RowBox[{"const_", ",", "state_"}], "]"}], ":=", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
    "multiply", " ", "a", " ", "state", " ", "by", " ", "some", " ", 
     "constant"}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", 
   RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"TermScale", "[", 
       RowBox[{"const", ",", "#"}], "]"}], "&"}], " ", ",", "state"}], 
    "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StateScale", "[", "const_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"StateScale", "[", 
      RowBox[{"const", ",", "#"}], "]"}], "&"}]}], ";"}], 
  "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"TermQuery", "[", "x_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
     RowBox[{
     "Attempts", " ", "to", " ", "check", " ", "if", " ", "x", " ", "matches",
       " ", "the", " ", "form", " ", "of", " ", "a", " ", 
      RowBox[{"Term", ".", " ", "Returns"}], " ", "a", " ", "boolean", " ", 
      RowBox[{"value", "."}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"If", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"ListQ", "[", "x", "]"}], " ", "&&", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Length", "[", "x", "]"}], "==", "2"}], " ", "&&", " ", 
       RowBox[{"ListQ", "[", 
        RowBox[{"x", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], " ", "&&", " ", 
       RowBox[{"NumberQ", "[", 
        RowBox[{"x", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ",", "True", ",", "False"}],
      "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"TermVanishingQuery", "[", "x_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
     RowBox[{
     "checks", " ", "if", " ", "x", " ", "matches", " ", "the", " ", "form", 
      " ", "of", " ", "a", " ", "Term", " ", "and", " ", "has", " ", "a", " ",
       "vanishing", " ", 
      RowBox[{"amplitude", ".", " ", "Returns"}], " ", "a", " ", "boolean", 
      " ", 
      RowBox[{"value", "."}]}], " ", "*)"}], 
    RowBox[{"If", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"TermQuery", "[", "x", "]"}], " ", "&&", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"x", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "==", "0"}]}], ",", "True", ",", 
      "False"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], 
  "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StatePrune", "[", "state_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
     RowBox[{
     "Removes", " ", "terms", " ", "with", " ", "vanishing", " ", 
      "amplitude"}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", 
    RowBox[{"Return", "[", "\n", 
     RowBox[{"Delete", "[", 
      RowBox[{"state", ",", 
       RowBox[{"Position", "[", 
        RowBox[{"state", ",", 
         RowBox[{"_", "?", "TermVanishingQuery"}]}], "]"}]}], "]"}], "\n", 
     "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StateOrder", "[", "state_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
     RowBox[{
     "Orders", " ", "the", " ", "terms", " ", "of", " ", "a", " ", "state", 
      " ", "by", " ", "their", " ", "quantum", " ", "numbers"}], " ", "*)"}], 
    "\n", 
    RowBox[{"Return", "[", 
     RowBox[{"SortBy", "[", 
      RowBox[{"state", ",", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"#", "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "&"}], ")"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
   ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StateRedistributeAmps", "[", "state_", "]"}], ":=", "\n", 
    RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
      "Sequentially", " ", "goes", " ", "through", " ", "a", " ", "list", " ",
        "of", " ", "Terms", " ", "and", " ", "modifies", " ", "their", " ", 
       "amplitudes", " ", "as", " ", 
       RowBox[{"follows", ":", "\n", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"If", " ", "Terms", " ", "j", " ", "and", " ", "j"}], "+", 
         RowBox[{
         "1", " ", "have", " ", "the", " ", "same", " ", "quantum", " ", 
          "numbers"}]}]}]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
      "and", " ", "have", " ", "amplitudes", " ", "A", " ", "and", " ", "B", 
       " ", "respectively"}], ",", "\n", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
       "then", " ", "the", " ", "amplitude", " ", "of", " ", "Term", " ", "j",
         " ", "is", " ", "set", " ", "to", " ", "zero", " ", "and", " ", 
        "the", " ", "amplitude", " ", "of", " ", "Term", " ", "j"}], "+", 
       RowBox[{"1", " ", "is", " ", "set", " ", "to", " ", "A"}], "+", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"B", ".", "\n", "This"}], " ", "has", " ", "the", " ", 
        "effect", " ", "of", " ", "consolidating", " ", "*", "neighboring", 
        "*", " ", "like", " ", "terms", " ", "into", " ", "a", " ", "single", 
        " ", "term", " ", "plus", " ", "vanishing", "\n", "terms", " ", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{"to", " ", "be", " ", "deleted"}], ")"}], "."}]}]}]}], " ", 
     "*)"}], "\n", 
    RowBox[{"Block", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"outputState", ",", "pos"}], "}"}], ",", "\n", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"outputState", "=", "state"}], ";", "\n", 
       RowBox[{"If", "[", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"Length", "[", "outputState", "]"}], "<=", "1"}], ",", "\n", 
         RowBox[{"Return", "[", "outputState", "]"}], "\n", ",", "\n", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"For", "[", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"pos", "=", "2"}], ",", 
            RowBox[{"pos", "<=", 
             RowBox[{"Length", "[", "outputState", "]"}]}], ",", 
            RowBox[{"pos", "++"}], ",", "\n", 
            RowBox[{"If", "[", 
             RowBox[{
              RowBox[{
               RowBox[{"outputState", "[", 
                RowBox[{"[", 
                 RowBox[{"pos", ",", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], "==", 
               RowBox[{"outputState", "[", 
                RowBox[{"[", 
                 RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{"pos", "-", "1"}], ",", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
              "\n", 
              RowBox[{
               RowBox[{
                RowBox[{"outputState", "[", 
                 RowBox[{"[", 
                  RowBox[{"pos", ",", "2"}], "]"}], "]"}], "+=", 
                RowBox[{"outputState", "[", 
                 RowBox[{"[", 
                  RowBox[{
                   RowBox[{"pos", "-", "1"}], ",", "2"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ";",
                "\n", 
               RowBox[{
                RowBox[{"outputState", "[", 
                 RowBox[{"[", 
                  RowBox[{
                   RowBox[{"pos", "-", "1"}], ",", "2"}], "]"}], "]"}], "=", 
                "0"}], ";"}]}], "]"}]}], "\n", "]"}], ";", "\n", 
          RowBox[{"Return", "[", "outputState", "]"}], ";"}]}], "\n", "]"}], 
       ";"}]}], "\n", "]"}]}], ";"}], 
  "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StateConsolidateTerms", "[", "state_", "]"}], ":=", "\n", 
    RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
     RowBox[{
     "Consolidates", " ", "like", " ", "Terms", " ", "of", " ", "a", " ", 
      "State", " ", "into", " ", "single", " ", 
      RowBox[{"Terms", "."}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", 
    RowBox[{"Return", "[", 
     RowBox[{"StatePrune", "[", 
      RowBox[{"StateRedistributeAmps", "[", 
       RowBox[{"StateOrder", "[", "state", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
   ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StateSimplifyAmps", "[", "state_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"attempts", " ", "to", " ", "Mathematica"}], "-", 
      RowBox[{"simplify", " ", "amplitudes"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", 
    RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"#", "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], ",", 
         RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
          RowBox[{"#", "[", 
           RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], "&"}], ",", 
      "state"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StateSimplify", "[", "state_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"StateSimplifyAmps", "[", 
     RowBox[{"StateConsolidateTerms", "[", "state", "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], 
  "\n"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"StateAdd", "[", 
     RowBox[{"stateA_", ",", "stateB_"}], "]"}], ":=", "\n", 
    RowBox[{"StateConsolidateTerms", "[", 
