 CellLabel->"In[25]:=",ExpressionUUID->"85fb4c30-b64e-4b14-b44c-b60d7a13449d"],

Cell["\<\
Link labels are (1,2,3). These are not to be confused with the color indices \
of Schwinger bosons that are used in the manuscript. Variables (i,j,k) stand \
for some ordering/permutation of the legs (1,2,3).

By hand, a basis ket would be expressed as |l12,l23,l31,l21,l32,l13,t>. 

As a Term in this script, the same Term is represented as \
{{l12,l23,l31,l21,l32,l13,t},1}, where the 1 at the end is the unit amplitude. 

The state \[Alpha] |l12,l23,l31,l21,l32,l13,t> + \[Beta] \
|L12,L23,L31,L21,L32,L13,T>, a linear combination of two terms, would be \
represented in this script as \
{{{l12,l23,l31,l21,l32,l13,t},\[Alpha]},{{L12,L23,L31,L21,L32,L13,T},\[Beta]}}\
. 

Please remember it is the QUANTUM NUMBERS FIRST in a Term, and the AMPLITUDE \
SECOND. This was adopted for convenience of reading output states that \
contain many terms; it is more orderly to align the terms on their quantum \
numbers.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.974785925091133*^9, 3.974785997673917*^9}, {
  3.974793631647284*^9, 
  3.974793653652781*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1aff1fd4-592b-405b-96c9-\
af70b009a6d9"]
}, Open  ]],

